section.section:
Notwithstanding § 7-104 of this title and after filing the application provided by § 7-103 of this title, property tax on any property that is transferred to a nonprofit charitable organization is abated from the date during the taxable year when the instrument transferring title to the organization is recorded if:
the property is transferred to a nonprofit charitable organization qualified under § 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code;
the property becomes exempt under this section;
the property has a value less than $300,000 as listed in the records of the Department on the date when the instrument transferring title to the organization is recorded; and
the nonprofit charitable organization provides the Department evidence of the property tax it actually paid or reimbursed at the property settlement.
